	(text_box "Bootstrap Cap (BOOTx - OUTx)\n\nFor STL110N10F7, since V_GS(th, max) = 4.5V and R_DS(on, max) spec'd at V_GS = 10V, VCC = 10V set in FW\n\nC_BOOT(min) >= (10*Q_g)/V_GS = (10*72nC)/10V = 72nF\n\nBut take 1uF from EVSPIN32G4 for plenty of safety buffer against voltage sag while remaining small enough to fully recharge when GLSx on"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 38.5974 0)
		(size 60.96 22.3626)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "10dc809b-c166-4dab-b09a-699ce9b6da8d")
	)
	(text_box "(Notes from Leo Before Task Assignment)\nVBUS Sensing (not totally necessar since we can assume it's constant, but it's nice to have)\n\nUse a voltage divider to scale the voltage down to an ADC-able range:\nVBUS = Vadc * (R1 + R2) / R2\n\n\nNOTE: DO IN CONTROL STAGE"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 434.34 140.462 0)
		(size 58.42 28.575)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2401c15f-675f-4fa4-9d03-7f28f111796b")
	)
	(text_box "gemini says 1nF b/w opp_c and opn_c, and 100pf from opp_c & opn_c to gnd\n\"to eliminate common-mode noise and differential noise\"\ni don't understand it.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 153.67 170.18 0)
		(size 41.91 11.43)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type color)
			(color 255 237 0 0.37)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "27c213af-fa26-43ad-afe1-12c69e5ebc31")
	)
	(text_box "(Notes from Leo Before Task Assignment)\nMotor Phase Current -> Shunt Resistor -> Current Amplifier -> ADC -> FW, with\nIphase = Vadc / (Gain × Rshunt), where V_shunt = Vadc / Gain\n-> Note that Vadc comes from the op amp AFTER it amplifies the signal\n\nThe result from an OPAMP will be fed into an ADC, then current is calculated. \nADC must be timer triggered, so sampling happens when the mosfet is conducting\n\nFor each phase, need:\n- 1 shunt resistor\n- 2 traces for current sense (OPAMP+ and OPAMP-) [also called Kelvin sense connections]"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 422.91 97.917 0)
		(size 69.215 39.37)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2d42525d-9d03-4a4c-b3ae-7fb964c30a34")
	)
	(text_box "!!!For info on how to configure op amp:\nAN5306 3.4.1, 3.4.3\n\n-> TODO: SCHEM"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 225.044 131.064 0)
		(size 44.958 10.0822)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
