		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "b4aaa026-2f6f-44be-95bf-561b36acb1aa")
	)
	(text_box "Asymmetric Gate Drive (GHSx/GLSx - GATE)\n\nTurn-off (gate pulled low) faster due to discharge thru D, so shoot-through avoided. Optional series R to damp voltage spikes in the path.\n\nTurn-on (gate pulled high) slowed by R to reduce voltage spikes\n\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 20.32 0)
		(size 60.96 18.2607)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d0eff5b7-bef8-48a7-ab31-f6eeb9fb9502")
	)
	(text_box "To-add (Notes from Leo Before Task Assignment):\n- Bootstrap Caps (BOOTx to OUTx)\n- (Local) Bus Decoupling Caps\n- Current Shunts (Internal Op Amps + ADC), unliuke SPx/SNx\n\n- VCC Bypass Caoacutir -> CONTROL STAGE\n- Bus Voltage Sensing (ADC Input, ST shows example) -> CONTROL STAGE\n- Protection for MOSFET Faults (SCREF for VDS protection?) -> CONSTROL STAGE"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 426.72 27.432 0)
		(size 65.405 27.94)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d2371bb0-04eb-4f5b-88e0-059d85ccecdb")
	)
	(text_box "Shunt Resistor\n\nFor a +/-50mV drop at +/-50A, R = 1.0m = 2.0m || 2.0m\n\nPair of parallel resistors, so 50A cts => 2.5W total (> 1.25W each)\n\nAt +/-2A, drop is +/-2mV, but use OPAMP configured in PGA mode (and voltage bias from internal DAC connection) to map to ADC range accordingly (bench testing will use way higher gain than while riding it fr)\n\nLayout Note: Using just regular 2-pin resistors despite the choice of symbol (4-pin kelvin sense)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 60.96 0)
		(size 60.96 32.5731)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
